content: Hi, so I recently installed arch Linux and want to use Firefox as my browser. However ever since I installed it, it takes a long time to launch the program. Also when I launch Firefox from the terminal I get this message "ATTENTION: default value of option mesa_glthread overridden by environment. Hopefully this makes some amount of sense to you.

title: Mozilla Maintenance Service version issue in Windows Apps & Features (Add/Remove Programs)
content:
When Mozilla Firefox is installed from the installer, it (optionally?) installs the Mozilla Maintenance Service.

In Windows, the Apps & Features (old: Add/Remove Programs) list adds the Mozilla Maintenance Service in the list of programs it can uninstall. The version number entered here is the version number of the Mozilla Maintenance Service upon installation.

Other methods of updating Firefox may update this service (current release version: 102.0.1.8221) - however, the version number contained within the Windows Apps & Features (old: Add/Remove Programs) list is never updated, and will instead display the original installation's version number.

I'd like to recommend that this be fixed, so that the version displayed in Apps & Features (old: Add/Remove Programs) always displays the current version installed.

(One of those flaky "software updater" utilities pointed this one out to me. "You have an old version of the Mozilla Maintenance Service installed!" yes, if you go by the numbers offered by the Apps & Features list...

title: Firefox Multi-Account Containers - MOVE to New Container Tab (Feature Request)
content:
I love Firefox Multi-Account Containers, but would really like to see one additional feature.

Directly below Open in New Container Tab I would like to have MOVE to new Container Tab (IE change the container for an existing tab). Currently I need to Open in New Container Tab and then delete the original tab. The existing configuration options are not sufficient, but should not be removed.

USE CASE: While surfing I may open a number of tabs related to a product or topic. I may then click on a link for a similar or different item (lets call it subject). At some point I may have a number of tabs open for 2 or more subjects. At this point I decide to move some to a new container to help me group the subjects. Currently this is 2 actions as opposed to 1.

Not sure if I am missing something. At this point none of the other add ins appear to, at least from their description, offer this function and I prefer to use as few add-ins as possible. I realize that I may need to relogin to the site to perform a purchase.
creator: RangerZ

title: Firefox hangs/freezes
content: Running Firefox on Linux Mint Mate 19.2 for several years. After updating FF to v. 102.0, started to experience random screen freezes- no response to mouse or keyboard input. Closing and restarting FF resets the browser but it eventually refreezes. Also since update, various profile elements such as font size do not display properly on some sites and settings on some sites are not retained on restart, as was the case in previous versions. Tabs added to home page do not launch until selected, where in previous versions of FF those sites loaded automatically when opening FF. Updating to v. 102.0.1 has made no difference.
creator: stevenartigas

title: Firefox Taskbar Icon requires two single clicks to open
content:
Hello there,

The Firefox Browser Icon that is on the taskbar requires two clicks to open the browser for the first time.

So when I single click the browser icon on the taskbar it doesn't open, so I need to click the icon again to open it. Its not that I need to double click it its just that every single time I need to click once then click it again to actually open the browser

Is there a way to fix this issue please?
creator: matthewdexter777
